Third-party components
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

This repository includes a generated kernel BTF header at
chronosynd-rs/crates/bpf/bpf/vmlinux.h, produced from a running Linux
kernel via "bpftool btf dump". That file consists solely of struct and
type definitions extracted from the kernel's BTF metadata. It is
included for the BPF program to compile against current kernel ABIs
and is not relicensed by ChronosynD; downstream users who redistribute
this header should consult their own legal counsel about kernel-derived
header reuse if they have any doubt.

All other third-party dependencies are pulled in at build time via
Cargo and uv, and their licenses apply at the points where they are
linked or imported.